result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (5th or 6th) and Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) was dismissed by the court.

  • Daniel Raymond Ryan was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Defendant shall pay a fine of $1,500.00 plus court costs in this matter.

Defendant shall not possess or consume any alcoholic beverages or nonprescription controlled substances, or any prescription medicine for which the defendant does not have a current prescription.
Defendant shall not enter into any establishment where the primary purpose is the sale of alcoholic beverages.

Defendant shall consent to a reasonable request of a law enforcement officer, based on probable cause, to submit to a breath, blood, saliva, or urine test for purposes of determining the quantity of alcohol or drugs in defendant's breath, blood, saliva, or urine.
Defendant shall participate in any and all counseling deemed appropriate by the Division of Community Corrections.
Defendant shall abide by all other terms and conditions of probation deemed appropriate by the Division of Community Corrections.
Defendant shall undergo an AODA assessment and follow through with all recommendations thereof.

timeConds.notes: 6 months incarceration in the Lafayette County jail with Huber privileges for medical issues/appointments.  Furlough granted 6:00 AM on the last day of each month.  Furlough goes until 6:00 PM on the second day of each month.

Case called at 9:08 AM.  Defendant Daniel Raymond Ryan in court with attorney Philip J. Brehm.   Katherine Findley appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant changes pleas from not guilty to no contest on count 1.  Attorney Brehm files Plea and Waiver.  Court questions Defendant re:  Plea and Waiver.  Court questions Attorney Brehm re:  Plea and Waiver.  Factual basis found.  Court finds DE enters plea knowingly, freely, voluntarily, and intelligently.  Court accepts plea and finds Defendant guilty.  State moves for joint recommendation of parties.  Attorney Brehm concurs with state.  Defendant makes statement to Court.  The Court grants motion of parties and adopts plea agreement, dismissing Count 2.  Sentence withheld, 3 years probation on Count 1.  Furlough granted 6:00 AM on the last day of each month.  Furlough goes until 6:00 PM on the second day of each month.  Defendant shall have huber privileges for medical appointments/issues.  Sentenced to 6 month jail-reporting on 1-5-17 at 6:00 PM.
